01:50.893 --> 01:54.852
And welcome to
the 38th annual NBA All-Star game...

01:54.963 --> 01:56.692
from Chicago Stadium.

01:56.799 --> 01:58.699
A standing-room-only crowd.

01:58.801 --> 02:03.238
A steal by Jordan.
He spun it away from the Mailman.

02:16.918 --> 02:19.386
Just needs a little time-out to reorganize.

02:19.487 --> 02:22.456
And the chances
of a West comeback are slipping away.

02:24.425 --> 02:26.450
Aguirre for three.

02:26.561 --> 02:28.927
I have never seen an All-Star game...

02:29.030 --> 02:31.624
that had such spectacular passing...

02:31.732 --> 02:33.893
and plays,
and thundering plays like this.

02:34.001 --> 02:36.401
They're beginning to hang, Billy.

02:37.505 --> 02:39.939
Ah, what a way to end this ball game.

02:54.988 --> 02:58.389
Right now, I wanna, you know,
play in the NBA...

02:58.491 --> 03:01.585
like anybody else would wanna be.

03:02.629 --> 03:04.893
That's who -
That's something...

03:04.998 --> 03:07.660
I dream and think
about all the time -

03:07.767 --> 03:09.666
playing in the NBA.

03:15.608 --> 03:17.940
He's just doing something
that he loves so much.

03:18.978 --> 03:22.709
He just love it so much.
I'm just happy for him.

03:22.815 --> 03:24.715
If somebody can understand
the way William play...

03:24.817 --> 03:27.377
that'll make me feel
a lot better.

03:27.486 --> 03:30.421
The way they should have
understood the way I played.

03:38.696 --> 03:42.359
This Chicagoan
is making his seventh All-Star appearance.

03:42.467 --> 03:44.992
From the Detroit Pistons, 6'1 "...

03:45.103 --> 03:47.731
Isaiah Thomas!

03:50.241 --> 03:52.232
When I get in the NBA...

03:52.343 --> 03:55.278
the first thing I'm gonna do...

03:55.380 --> 03:59.009
I'm gonna see my mama, buy her a house...

03:59.117 --> 04:02.553
I'm gonna go there and make sure
my sister and my brother's okay.

04:02.654 --> 04:04.986
If we were okay or not.

04:05.089 --> 04:07.716
Probably get my dad...

04:07.824 --> 04:09.815
a Cadillac Oldsmobile...

04:09.927 --> 04:11.895
so he can cruise in the games.

04:11.995 --> 04:13.690
Something real long.

04:13.797 --> 04:15.856
Dominique.! Ooh.!

04:16.966 --> 04:19.935
He dreams about it.

04:20.036 --> 04:22.301
He look at those
basketball commercials...

04:22.406 --> 04:25.204
where they be advertising these Nike shoes?

04:25.309 --> 04:27.368
He'll tell his little, small brother...

04:27.477 --> 04:29.377
"Joe, Joe, that's me."

04:29.479 --> 04:33.813
So the West leads.
Thomas trying to go the distance. Loses it.

04:43.592 --> 04:47.221
I don't even think about
it, if he don't make it.

04:47.330 --> 04:49.628
Just 'cause I'm so -

04:49.732 --> 04:51.825
I'm so, you know,
focused in on him making it.

04:51.934 --> 04:53.834
I just know he'll make it.

05:30.038 --> 05:35.100
I'm off to Central...

05:35.209 --> 05:37.177
and the Congress
Expressway-

05:37.277 --> 05:41.236
a park over there where there are
some pretty talented young men.

05:41.348 --> 05:45.682
Earl Smith works downtown
as an insurance executive.

05:45.786 --> 05:49.882
On weekends he's an unofficial talent scout
for several area high schools.

05:55.562 --> 05:57.757
This is what you call
"beating the bushes."

05:57.865 --> 06:00.766
This is the job
of most of your freshmen coaches...

06:00.868 --> 06:04.963
and guys like me who -
who played a little bit of the game...

06:05.071 --> 06:08.563
who love trying to help young people
on the road to success.

06:10.643 --> 06:12.543
It's in! It's in!

06:14.347 --> 06:18.215
Today Earl spots Arthur Agee,
who just graduated from grammar school.

06:19.285 --> 06:22.880
He's got the quickest first step
that I've seen in about five years.

06:22.989 --> 06:24.889
His first step.

06:28.761 --> 06:32.457
I will bet you a steak dinner
in four years you'll be hearing from him.

06:32.564 --> 06:34.998
I don't even know anything about him.

06:49.881 --> 06:51.729
Several days later,

06:51.730 --> 06:53.578
Earl takes Arthur and his family
on a recruiting visit...

06:53.685 --> 06:57.121
to the high school
where NBA star Isiah Thomas played.

06:57.222 --> 06:59.247
The visit will give
St. Joseph's coaches...

06:59.357 --> 07:01.347
a chance to see Arthur perform.

07:10.301 --> 07:12.826
Your role today, Arthur...

07:12.937 --> 07:15.929
is to impress the coaches.

07:16.040 --> 07:18.065
Try not to be too fancy.

07:18.175 --> 07:20.643
Take the open shot when you have it.

07:21.679 --> 07:24.648
Play good defense
and make good passes.

07:24.748 --> 07:27.308
The rest of it,
just play natural, you know.

07:28.953 --> 07:32.820
I'm hoping I'm gonna go to St. Joe
and play...

07:32.922 --> 07:37.086
but first I gotta -
I gotta get my books straight.

07:37.193 --> 07:39.684
And...

07:39.796 --> 07:43.254
hopefully come out
and impress the coaches.

07:44.834 --> 07:47.701
Is it kinda scary?

07:47.804 --> 07:49.772
Yes, it is.

07:52.675 --> 07:56.304
I've never been to a school
way out before...

07:56.412 --> 08:00.643
and I would be going to a school
with different kids, different races.

08:02.518 --> 08:06.648
You can look at the scenery,
new friends to meet.

08:10.025 --> 08:12.255
What if Isiah's there today?

08:15.297 --> 08:18.095
Well, if he be there...

08:19.201 --> 08:21.328
I'll be shocked...

08:21.436 --> 08:23.961
'cause that'd be my first time
ever seeing him...

08:24.072 --> 08:26.768
Up close, you know, real life.

08:32.712 --> 08:36.547
Basketball has to be second
to your academics.

08:36.650 --> 08:38.710
If you don't get your grades,
you're not gonna play.

08:38.818 --> 08:43.347
If you work hard at the grades,
and if you work hard at basketball...

08:43.457 --> 08:46.255
then I would be able to help you
as far as going to college.

08:46.360 --> 08:48.328
And I guarantee this.

08:48.429 --> 08:51.830
I can't promise you where you're gonna go
and if you're gonna be a star...

08:51.933 --> 08:55.926
but I guarantee that I would help you
get into the school...

08:56.037 --> 08:58.527
that would be best for you.

08:58.638 --> 09:00.936
I'm making a commitment to you...

09:01.041 --> 09:04.067
if you make a commitment
to being part of this kind of a program.

09:09.849 --> 09:13.444
Out of all of the kids
at the St. Joseph Basketball Camp...

09:13.553 --> 09:16.579
there are a few like Arthur
that Coach Pingatore is recruiting.

09:20.527 --> 09:23.724
It was like million of guys
trying to be better than the other...

09:23.830 --> 09:27.321
but, to me,
I was better than all of them...

09:27.433 --> 09:29.901
except Isiah.

09:30.002 --> 09:34.496
It gives me great pleasure to introduce
to you a graduate of St. Joe's...

09:34.607 --> 09:37.167
high school all-American...

09:37.276 --> 09:40.768
All-American from Indiana University...

09:40.879 --> 09:43.109
five-time NBA All-Star...

09:43.215 --> 09:45.410
Isiah Thomas.

09:45.517 --> 09:49.351
Hello. How are you?

09:49.455 --> 09:53.653
In everybody's neighborhood,
there's a guy who can really play.

09:53.759 --> 09:55.658
He can shoot the lights out.

09:55.760 --> 09:59.355
Every time down the court -
Swish, swish, swish!

09:59.464 --> 10:02.627
Then he goes to St. Joseph high School...

10:02.734 --> 10:05.760
and the guy gets cut.

10:05.870 --> 10:09.931
You say, "But Tom was real good.
Why did he get cut?'"

10:10.041 --> 10:13.738
See, Tom didn't learn
the fundamentals of team basketball...

10:13.845 --> 10:16.313
which is what you're learning
how to play.

10:31.328 --> 10:33.796
He told my daddy
that he knew I could play...

10:33.897 --> 10:35.831
so he just had to play me hard.

10:51.882 --> 10:55.715
I can see the playground in him.
I can see talent.

10:55.818 --> 10:58.116
But I don't see the confidence.

11:02.692 --> 11:06.184
With Isiah, I just knew
he was gonna be a great one.

11:06.295 --> 11:11.198
He had that total combination
of personality, confidence, talent...

11:11.300 --> 11:13.359
intelligence.

11:13.469 --> 11:17.735
I think I see it in one kid
that's coming here.

11:17.840 --> 11:22.208
He flows with a smoothness
and confidence...

11:22.310 --> 11:24.210
and strength...

11:24.312 --> 11:26.837
that you don't see in every kid.

11:26.948 --> 11:30.008
But he could become a great player.

11:39.994 --> 11:43.521
You gotta take a shot.
Always work it. You can't block it.

11:48.603 --> 11:50.730
Ohh.!

11:50.839 --> 11:52.965
I just bang him and bruise him.

11:53.073 --> 11:56.338
I'm trying to let him know right now
you gonna get hit, get knocked down...

11:56.443 --> 11:59.412
you gonna get banged around,
so you better get used to it now.

12:00.581 --> 12:02.549
Stop it. One-hand hook.

12:04.318 --> 12:07.913
All these basketball dreams I had,
they gone.

12:08.021 --> 12:11.286
All I see -All my dreams in him now.

12:11.392 --> 12:14.122
I want him to make it so bad,
I don't know what to do.

12:16.196 --> 12:19.654
They want to play basketball
and stuff, that was always okay.

12:20.933 --> 12:24.630
But I was gonna make sure all of 'em
got through high school.

12:24.737 --> 12:28.730
A high school diploma
was very important to me.

12:32.712 --> 12:36.842
My mother,
she was like mother and father to me.

12:36.949 --> 12:41.648
She don't want me really
hanging around over here that much...

12:41.754 --> 12:43.722
'cause of the gangs.

12:44.957 --> 12:47.255
I feel if I go to St. Joseph...

12:47.360 --> 12:50.453
I'll at least get a good chance
to go to a good college.

12:50.562 --> 12:52.894
That would be good for me.

13:02.641 --> 13:04.632
That was my first son.

13:05.744 --> 13:09.180
I said, "That's Daddy's man, '"
so we just started calling him "Man. '"

13:09.281 --> 13:11.249
Get around it!

13:12.784 --> 13:14.945
I could have been a good college player.

13:15.053 --> 13:18.681
Most likely
I would have made it to the pros.

13:18.789 --> 13:21.622
But, you know, once I had my son...

13:21.725 --> 13:24.353
I knew then something good
was gonna come out of it.

13:24.462 --> 13:26.726
I think the talent gonna be passed on.

13:33.103 --> 13:37.540
He told me, "I'm so scared of growing up."
I said, "Why?"

13:37.641 --> 13:41.668
he said a grown-up has so many problems.
"I got so many things on my mind."

13:41.779 --> 13:44.441
I just want Arthur to have more...

13:44.548 --> 13:46.914
you know,
have a better life than what I had.

13:47.017 --> 13:50.315
I don't want him experiencing
bad things that I went through in life.

14:30.459 --> 14:34.156
Austin Boulevard
will be the next stop. Austin is next.

14:34.263 --> 14:36.322
Like Isiah Thomas before them...

14:36.431 --> 14:39.559
both Arthur and William make
a three-hour round trip each day...

14:39.668 --> 14:42.569
between the city and St. Joseph's.

14:42.671 --> 14:45.468
That was strange for me
going out to a far-out school.

14:45.573 --> 14:50.203
I saw a rug, flowers, clean hallways...

14:50.311 --> 14:53.439
things that I didn't see
in an ordinary school.

15:17.470 --> 15:20.496
Gotta move! Gotta move!

15:20.607 --> 15:22.507
Come on.

15:24.945 --> 15:26.845
- Three, four, five or 10?
- Ten.

15:26.947 --> 15:28.881
You got it. Three, four, five?

15:28.982 --> 15:32.645
Arthur wins the starting
point-guard position on the freshmen team.

15:32.752 --> 15:37.280
Agee, I want you to find
in that warm-up number two.

15:37.390 --> 15:39.620
Brown, number three.

15:39.726 --> 15:42.217
Ettmeyer, four.

15:42.329 --> 15:46.128
Hey, Arthur, you know
if you miss free throws...

15:46.231 --> 15:48.699
they count 'em up,
and you have to pay 15 cents.

15:48.801 --> 15:50.598
Then if you don't pay
it, they gonna make you

15:50.599 --> 15:52.396
run 50 laps, and still
you have to pay the money.

15:52.504 --> 15:55.473
- You still gotta pay the money?
- That's way out.

16:00.679 --> 16:04.012
When Arthur first started at St.
Joseph's...

16:04.116 --> 16:06.482
he was a good kid,
from what we saw...

16:06.585 --> 16:08.883
but he was very immature.

16:08.988 --> 16:11.548
He might have been a little more
disruptive, speaking out...

16:11.657 --> 16:13.749
getting into childish things.

16:15.827 --> 16:18.694
He wasn't used to the discipline
and the control.

16:18.796 --> 16:22.232
He reverted back to, maybe,
his environment, where he came from.

16:24.802 --> 16:28.704
I just never been around
a lot of white people and...

16:28.806 --> 16:33.106
it was different, because at a black school
I could associate with the people.

16:33.211 --> 16:35.145
They talk the way I talk.

16:35.246 --> 16:38.977
It was a little hard,
but I can adjust to it.

16:40.485 --> 16:43.510
You can see there was talent there.

16:43.620 --> 16:46.350
We kept saying up in the stands,
"Get the ball to Arthur...

16:46.456 --> 16:48.754
because he's going to do it for you. '"

16:48.859 --> 16:51.521
And sure enough, they gave him the ball
with seconds on the clock.

16:59.803 --> 17:03.136
I noticed a change immediately
after he started going out there.

17:03.240 --> 17:07.506
To see your child mature, you say,
"Oh, maybe this is good for him."

17:20.790 --> 17:24.351
William begins
his freshman season on St. Joe's varsity...

17:24.460 --> 17:26.451
the top-ranked squad in the state.

17:35.738 --> 17:38.263
He's already received several letters...

17:38.374 --> 17:40.773
from Division I schools -

17:40.875 --> 17:44.470
Marquette and Rice and Creighton,
Illinois State...

17:44.579 --> 17:46.479
to name a few.

17:50.051 --> 17:53.077
Beat him! Beat him! Beat him!
Keep back!

17:56.725 --> 18:00.684
Hold it up! hold it up!
You're killing us!

18:00.795 --> 18:03.263
Why did he get to the ball before you?

18:04.866 --> 18:08.426
He asks me, do I wanna be
a great player? And I keep saying yeah.

18:08.535 --> 18:11.504
He said, "For four years,
I'm gonna be on you every day."

18:11.605 --> 18:14.597
So he said, "You might as well
get used to it now."

18:14.708 --> 18:17.939
hard left. No, no. Go hard left.

18:18.045 --> 18:22.004
Right, I know you can do it.
Left, you can't. All right? Go hard.

18:23.650 --> 18:26.278
Not bad. Do it again.

18:31.692 --> 18:34.320
If you look at Matthew,
and again he's saying...

18:34.428 --> 18:37.624
at the time the kingdom of heaven
will be like this.

18:37.730 --> 18:40.563
This is how Matthew's gonna use Jesus.
This is how he's gonna start it out.

18:40.666 --> 18:44.102
What this is saying
is you have to take the faith-

18:44.203 --> 18:47.536
When I first came out here,
it was, like, "I wanna go home.

18:47.640 --> 18:50.609
Is this really the right school for me?'"

18:50.710 --> 18:54.612
But every little thing you do
that go against their rule...

18:54.714 --> 18:56.705
you have detention.

18:56.816 --> 18:59.717
And they'll suspend you quick
at the school too.

18:59.819 --> 19:01.719
They'll suspend you quick.

19:01.821 --> 19:04.619
The kids that are willing to do it...

19:05.758 --> 19:07.554
are gonna take something away

19:07.555 --> 19:09.352
that will help them for
the rest of their life.

19:09.461 --> 19:12.225
The kids that are not willing to do it...

19:12.330 --> 19:14.457
for whatever reason, uh...

19:14.566 --> 19:16.796
are not gonna be very successful
as far as here.

19:16.902 --> 19:20.770
The civil rights movement
started up in the '50s.

19:20.872 --> 19:23.070
When William first entered St. Joe's...

19:23.075 --> 19:26.403
tests revealed he was working
on a fourth or fifth-grade level.

19:27.813 --> 19:30.373
I could see that he had the potential...

19:30.482 --> 19:34.077
but because he was shy, it seemed as though
no one was trying to reach him.

19:35.786 --> 19:39.688
Sister Marilyn told me,
"You have to be one good ballplayer...

19:39.790 --> 19:42.281
to get in this school with these grades. '"

19:42.393 --> 19:45.055
- What war beginning in the '60s?
- Vietnam.

19:45.162 --> 19:49.292
At the end of the year,
he had gone four grades above...

19:49.400 --> 19:52.699
just in the way he listened and learned.

19:55.973 --> 19:57.873
Back in grammar school...

19:57.975 --> 20:01.035
academics really didn't matter
too much to me at all.

20:03.113 --> 20:07.481
It was playing ball for the team-
really, we was the standouts in the school.

20:07.584 --> 20:10.644
If you showed up in class,
that was good enough for them.

20:10.753 --> 20:13.745
I was just going to school for the girls.

20:13.857 --> 20:15.825
Trip out with your friends...

20:15.925 --> 20:19.053
get out, go play some more basketball.

20:19.162 --> 20:21.756
That was basically it.

20:25.401 --> 20:29.770
Arthur also entered St. Joe's
on a fourth or fifth-grade level.

20:29.873 --> 20:33.706
Nobody in their right mind
is crazy about school.

20:33.809 --> 20:35.743
If the president brought
up a thing right now

20:35.744 --> 20:37.677
that say, "Close all schools"...

20:37.779 --> 20:41.215
do you think any kids would be trying
to go out there, stand on a picket line...

20:41.316 --> 20:45.275
and wave and get billboards...

20:45.387 --> 20:47.685
saying, "Reopen schools"?

20:47.789 --> 20:50.451
Nice and tall, guys.
Now, don't look at the flash.

20:50.559 --> 20:53.460
Arthur was in
the lower group of the general program.

20:53.562 --> 20:55.689
Okay, fellas. Good.

20:55.797 --> 20:58.823
At the end of the year,
he was still in the lower group.

20:58.934 --> 21:00.902
One, two, three.!

21:04.071 --> 21:06.938
For Arthur, the season is over.

21:07.041 --> 21:10.204
His freshman team finished second
in the conference.

21:10.311 --> 21:13.838
William's varsity is rolling
through the play-offs.

21:25.660 --> 21:29.892
Against Proviso East,
William plays his best game yet.

21:32.299 --> 21:36.429
And the Chargers move a step closer to
going downstate to compete for the title.

21:41.207 --> 21:44.973
St. Joe's made it downstate
five of the last six years.

21:45.078 --> 21:48.172
The one thing we haven't done
is win a state tournament.

21:49.582 --> 21:54.485
Man, that'd be a big thing
if I could go downstate as a freshman.

21:54.587 --> 21:57.351
Isiah was good enough
to start on the varsity as a freshman.

21:57.457 --> 22:01.756
I didn't do it because I was worried
about bringing him along too rapidly.

22:01.860 --> 22:05.023
I think by not doing it,
it cost us a state championship.

22:09.902 --> 22:14.532
In the sectional finals,
Fenwick challenges St. Joe's title hopes.

22:14.640 --> 22:18.599
But in the second quarter,
William steps up.

22:19.845 --> 22:21.779
With his brother Curtis looking on...

22:21.880 --> 22:25.839
William scores 16 points to lead
the Chargers to the sectional title.

22:28.687 --> 22:33.385
From Chicago, it's The
Sports Writers On TV.

22:33.491 --> 22:37.928
I think I may have seen
the next Isiah Thomas.

22:38.029 --> 22:42.591
St. Joe of Westchester
has a kid named William Gates...

22:42.700 --> 22:45.134
who is starting as a freshman.

22:45.236 --> 22:47.704
Remember, you heard it first
from Bill Gleason.

22:47.805 --> 22:50.740
Put it in your memory banks,
ladies and gentlemen.

22:50.842 --> 22:53.436
William Gates.

22:56.814 --> 23:00.476
In the supersectionals,
St. Joe's meets DeSalles...

23:00.584 --> 23:03.815
to decide who will go downstate.

23:03.920 --> 23:06.036
William plays more like
an intimidated freshman

23:06.037 --> 23:08.152
than a freshman sensation.

23:10.394 --> 23:14.592
Six-nine senior all-American
Eric Anderson dominates St. Joe's.

23:18.402 --> 23:21.997
But in the third quarter,
William takes over again.

23:23.106 --> 23:26.837
He fires over Anderson
and is fouled.

23:29.378 --> 23:31.778
William's 13 points
in the second half...

23:31.881 --> 23:34.179
pull the Chargers to within four.

23:37.853 --> 23:41.380
With less than two minutes to play,
it's a must-score.

23:52.368 --> 23:54.632
St. Joe's jump shot falls short.

24:00.008 --> 24:02.442
Eric Anderson.!

24:18.059 --> 24:20.789
Despite the loss,
William's gutty performance...

24:20.895 --> 24:22.795
bodes well for next year.

24:22.897 --> 24:24.160
There will be an announcement

24:24.161 --> 24:26.093
on ticket sales immediately
following the game.

24:29.970 --> 24:32.768
Rewriting 7,300 times 10...

24:32.873 --> 24:36.536
to the negative fifth
in scientific notation.

24:36.643 --> 24:38.702
Who wants that problem?

24:38.812 --> 24:40.712
- I do.
- Go ahead, William.

24:40.814 --> 24:42.748
- 7.3...
- 7.3...

24:42.850 --> 24:46.081
- times 10 to the third.
- Times 10 to the third times-

24:46.186 --> 24:48.381
- 10 to the negative second.
- Is that good!

24:48.489 --> 24:50.389
Very good.

24:50.491 --> 24:53.426
When I went out there,
I was very intimidated...

24:53.527 --> 24:56.461
'cause I just knew that everybody out there
was just smarter than me.

24:57.497 --> 25:00.227
As the year went on...

25:00.333 --> 25:02.631
and I was making
an "A'"and "B'"honor roll...

25:02.735 --> 25:05.932
I just felt like,
"hey, I'm just as good as them. '"

25:07.340 --> 25:09.638
Now what you have to identify-

25:09.742 --> 25:13.473
Both William and Arthur
have partial scholarships from St. Joe's.

25:13.579 --> 25:16.070
The rest of William's tuition
is paid for by Cycle...

25:16.182 --> 25:18.082
a Cabrini Green organization.

25:18.184 --> 25:21.210
But Cycle can't cover
this year's tuition increase.

25:21.320 --> 25:24.811
I was called on
by Brother Edwin Duprais.

25:24.923 --> 25:27.050
He was trying to raise money
to help kids...

25:27.159 --> 25:29.855
that couldn't otherwise go
to those kind of schools.

25:29.961 --> 25:32.156
It really touched a soft
spot in my heart...

25:32.264 --> 25:36.166
and so I decided that my husband and I
would participate on a personal basis.

25:36.268 --> 25:39.533
William was selected as the kid...

25:39.638 --> 25:42.505
that was able to go to school,
based on our contribution.

25:42.607 --> 25:44.632
- Nice to see you.
- Nice to see you.

25:44.743 --> 25:49.043
You played a great game. I want you to
meet our friends Liz Duncan, Tom Paris.

25:49.147 --> 25:51.047
- Nice game.
- William Gates.

25:51.149 --> 25:53.378
With continuing support
from Patricia Wier...

25:53.484 --> 25:56.942
William is assured
that his entire education at St. Joe's...

25:57.054 --> 25:59.284
will be free.

26:03.661 --> 26:06.789
Arthur's family is paying
for half of his tuition...

26:06.897 --> 26:10.355
and the increase comes
at an especially bad time.

26:10.467 --> 26:12.992
Worked for Sara Lee, got laid off.

26:13.103 --> 26:17.369
Uh, worked for Scala's Meat Packing.
Got laid off there. You know.

26:17.474 --> 26:21.068
You look around your house,
you see your food getting low. Okay?

26:21.177 --> 26:26.137
And you got your bills due here,
your bills due there.

26:30.019 --> 26:32.487
I got called down to the office.

26:32.589 --> 26:34.682
Brother Leo wanted to talk to me.

26:34.791 --> 26:38.454
He was telling me about how much,
certain money my mama had to pay...

26:38.561 --> 26:40.620
for me to stay in school.

26:40.730 --> 26:44.188
They say if she don't have it by this time,
you gotta stay out till she pay it.

26:44.300 --> 26:47.292
I was staying out, like,
two and three weeks and stuff.

26:47.403 --> 26:49.927
By the end of the freshman year...

26:50.038 --> 26:54.338
whatever balance there was for
tuition was never taken care of.

26:54.443 --> 26:56.877
Consequently,
going into the sophomore year...

26:56.979 --> 26:59.243
we had the balance
plus the new tuition...

26:59.348 --> 27:02.078
so that it was going to continue
to become a problem.

27:02.184 --> 27:05.585
Whatever scout that they have come out
to these different neighborhoods...

27:05.687 --> 27:08.155
and scout out
these little basketball players...

27:08.257 --> 27:11.693
and get 'em to come to their school
and offer them these scholarships.

27:11.793 --> 27:14.261
Then once they get out there,
the story is totally different.

27:14.263 --> 27:16.019
I was under the impression
that Arthur would

27:16.032 --> 27:17.799
have help as far as
getting to school.

27:17.899 --> 27:20.833
Arthur would have help
in getting his books.

27:20.935 --> 27:23.096
But, see, none of that occur.

27:23.204 --> 27:27.971
Finally, with the Agees
owing $ 1,500 in back payments...

27:28.075 --> 27:31.010
St. Joseph's forced Arthur
to leave the school.

27:33.014 --> 27:36.347
I thought Pingatore and them
would help me out, but -

27:41.322 --> 27:44.052
You have to draw the line
because, as I said...

27:44.158 --> 27:48.116
tuition is something that,
as a school, we depend on...

27:48.228 --> 27:50.458
for 90%% of our revenue.

27:50.563 --> 27:53.589
I guess he thought I wasn't gonna be
that big of a ballplayer.

27:53.700 --> 27:57.136
So why would he just waste
some money on me staying there?

27:57.237 --> 27:59.205
Or, you know, he thought
I wasn't gonna grow.

27:59.306 --> 28:02.867
He kept on saying,
"When are you gonna grow?"

28:02.976 --> 28:04.944
Well, I don't know.

28:06.646 --> 28:10.104
If I had known that all of this
was gonna lead to this...

28:10.216 --> 28:12.946
Arthur would have never went
to St. Joseph's.

28:13.053 --> 28:16.022
I mean, if I had known that he was gonna
have to go through this type of pain...

28:16.122 --> 28:18.021
and myself-the anguish of it...

28:18.123 --> 28:21.752
and then to put him out
in the middle of a school year-

28:51.622 --> 28:54.113
I.D.'s, ladies and gentlemen.

28:55.827 --> 28:57.727
All right. Okay, okay. All right.

28:59.997 --> 29:02.090
Can't take no beepers in here.

29:02.200 --> 29:04.725
Give me my beeper, man.

29:06.104 --> 29:07.901
Mr. Wade, I need to see you
at the front door.

29:08.005 --> 29:11.600
Now where you gonna go?
Your friend go to jail. No beepers in here.

29:11.709 --> 29:13.609
Don't make no scene.

29:13.711 --> 29:16.838
Arthur is accepted
at the public high school near his home.

29:16.947 --> 29:21.646
He's been out of school for two months
and lost a whole semester's credit.

29:23.487 --> 29:25.381
Here you have a youngster caught

29:25.382 --> 29:27.924
in the middle of two
separate school systems.

29:28.024 --> 29:30.322
Had he stayed at St. Joseph's...

29:30.427 --> 29:33.692
he would have been able to receive
credit for that first semester.

29:34.798 --> 29:37.699
Doesn't seem fair,
but then that's the system.

29:39.369 --> 29:40.939
If he was going out there
and he was playing

29:40.952 --> 29:42.532
like they had predicted
him to play...

29:42.639 --> 29:44.538
he wouldn't be at Marshall.

29:44.640 --> 29:47.370
Economics wouldn't have had anything
to do with him not being at St. Joe's.

29:47.476 --> 29:48.846
Somebody would have made some kind of

29:48.847 --> 29:50.809
arrangement, and the kid
would've still been there.

29:50.913 --> 29:54.178
He's not making it like they thought he was
gonna make it on the basketball court...

29:54.283 --> 29:56.217
so he's not there, simple as that.

29:56.318 --> 29:59.082
It doesn't take no brilliant person
to figure that out.

30:03.459 --> 30:07.361
It's mid-season
when Arthur joins the sophomore team.

30:07.463 --> 30:10.864
He was so depressed and devastated,
he just closed himself off in the room.

30:10.966 --> 30:16.369
I would go in there and tell him
every day, "hey, things will look up. '"

30:18.573 --> 30:21.167
Coming off the bench,
Arthur wears number 11...

30:21.276 --> 30:23.403
Isiah Thomas's number.

30:35.256 --> 30:37.724
What kind of techniques were being used...

30:37.826 --> 30:40.852
to take away the freedoms
that had been earned?

30:40.962 --> 30:43.259
- Jeannetta.
- Poll tax.

30:43.363 --> 30:46.560
Poll tax. Okay, Arthur,
what other techniques were used...

30:46.667 --> 30:49.295
to keep black Americans from voting?

30:49.403 --> 30:51.303
Um-

30:51.405 --> 30:53.703
You could almost forget
about his being there.

30:53.807 --> 30:56.367
That's how quiet he really was.

30:56.477 --> 30:59.935
I think the transition
had something to do with it.

31:03.784 --> 31:06.252
In comparing
Marshall high School to St. Joseph...

31:06.353 --> 31:08.287
I don't think
that there is any comparison.

31:08.388 --> 31:10.856
People can afford
to send their children there.

31:10.957 --> 31:14.256
They can afford to put money
into the school.

31:14.360 --> 31:16.294
Once they walk in those doors...

31:16.395 --> 31:19.592
they walk in there to get that diploma
and to go on to college.

31:19.699 --> 31:23.795
Whereas our students,
if they get out of high school...

31:23.903 --> 31:26.667
a lot of them,
it's an accomplishment.

31:26.772 --> 31:30.367
Trinomial. What's this gonna be?
Both of these are what?

31:30.476 --> 31:33.411
If he wanna go back next year...

31:33.513 --> 31:35.811
he gonna go back, if I have to beg.

31:38.417 --> 31:41.874
Because, uh, I wanna help him
with his little dream.

31:47.659 --> 31:51.095
Arthur's mother, Sheila,
has lost her minimum-wage job...

31:51.196 --> 31:53.096
as a nurse's assistant...

31:53.198 --> 31:55.462
because of chronic back pain.

31:58.904 --> 32:01.930
It's just a real hard area
to live in, period.

32:02.040 --> 32:04.508
And as far as raising kids -

32:05.911 --> 32:08.675
kids don't even have a playground
or play area...

32:08.780 --> 32:11.680
anything constructive to do
in the neighborhood.

32:11.782 --> 32:14.910
But you see why half of them
become gangbangers, you know.

32:15.019 --> 32:18.079
Because it's nothing constructive
in the neighborhood for 'em.

32:22.226 --> 32:26.219
So now it's, like, you more or less
got to keep your kids close to you...

32:26.330 --> 32:28.491
and watch 'em at all times.

32:48.551 --> 32:51.782
In June, after 20 years of marriage...

32:51.888 --> 32:54.516
Arthur's dad leaves the family.

