You, most likely,
have at least torn this cartilage...

46:34.515 --> 46:36.380
the inside cartilage of your knee.

46:37.651 --> 46:41.916
And you may have
a ligament tear in your knee, okay?

46:43.289 --> 46:46.588
If the ligament is torn, William,
you would miss this year...

46:46.693 --> 46:48.661
entirely.

46:48.762 --> 46:52.698
This is a lot to happen to you
at an early age. A lot.

46:52.799 --> 46:54.733
I think, if all goes well...

46:54.834 --> 46:56.802
you'll be able to come back.

47:11.850 --> 47:14.512
Everything was just going great.

47:15.554 --> 47:17.454
Now this.

47:23.195 --> 47:25.663
All you guys can't get large.

47:26.999 --> 47:29.194
- Somebody accidentally-
- What's up, man?

47:29.301 --> 47:32.566
Somebody gotta wear medium. You little
skinny guys wanna get in a large.

47:32.671 --> 47:34.571
What the other guys gonna put on?

47:34.673 --> 47:37.072
Watch that boy.
He'll steal your drawers.

47:37.175 --> 47:41.305
Junior year, Arthur makes varsity
for the Marshall Commandos.

47:57.228 --> 47:59.696
This is the year, right?

47:59.797 --> 48:02.129
This is it.
All righty.

48:02.233 --> 48:04.428
Not too bad.

48:04.535 --> 48:06.365
Fine.

48:13.276 --> 48:16.905
Back home,
the family's troubles have worsened.

48:17.013 --> 48:19.709
Now I'm on welfare...

48:19.816 --> 48:21.784
that I wasn't on then.

48:22.819 --> 48:27.347
And trying to live month-to-month
on something like that is very hard.

48:27.457 --> 48:30.187
You have three growing kids
that need this...

48:30.293 --> 48:32.523
and you have bills to pay...

48:32.629 --> 48:36.086
and it's just not enough
to make ends meet.

48:39.635 --> 48:43.935
Man.! Sweetie, is Man in there?

48:44.039 --> 48:46.803
I was never raised on welfare.

48:46.909 --> 48:50.208
My mother and father both worked.

48:53.649 --> 48:56.618
We was cut off for three months.

48:56.719 --> 48:59.244
We was cut off aid complete
with no income.

48:59.355 --> 49:01.482
So, therefore,
do you know what happened?

49:01.590 --> 49:04.023
Our lights were cut off.
Our gas was cut off.

49:04.125 --> 49:06.320
And we were sittin' in the dark.

49:16.004 --> 49:19.770
They had cut me off because
I failed to meet an appointment.

49:28.082 --> 49:31.415
It hurt everybody.
It changed everybody's attitude.

49:31.519 --> 49:35.079
That you can have something today
and it's gone tomorrow.

49:37.291 --> 49:40.385
So you know what the system
is saying to me?

49:40.494 --> 49:44.555
Do you know what it's saying
to a lot of women in my predicament?

49:44.665 --> 49:46.656
They don't care.

50:16.362 --> 50:19.820
The good news is
that your ligament looks fine.

50:19.932 --> 50:22.492
- Good.
- Okay? Your ligament looks fine.

50:22.602 --> 50:25.230
We can actually
sew the cartilage back.

50:25.338 --> 50:30.071
So you're looking at a minimum
of 12 weeks, maybe 16 weeks...

50:30.176 --> 50:32.905
before I'll let you play ball again.

50:33.011 --> 50:36.139
Possibly being able to play
by tournament time.

50:36.247 --> 50:38.147
Okay?

50:45.123 --> 50:48.115
I'm gonna slip you a little something
into the I.V...

50:48.226 --> 50:50.922
to kind of take the edge
off of things, okay?

50:51.029 --> 50:52.963
All right?

50:53.064 --> 50:55.294
- I can tell.
- Yeah.

50:55.400 --> 50:57.300
No doubt.

51:13.851 --> 51:16.786
- Let's turn him.
- Yeah, this way.

51:17.821 --> 51:20.051
If it stays there.

51:20.157 --> 51:23.684
Probably go with the right post here
and little stuff.

51:28.465 --> 51:32.093
The doctor told me he wasn't gonna even
try to get him ready to play this year.

51:32.201 --> 51:35.659
So what do you think
that goin' do to his career?

51:45.481 --> 51:47.949
I really thought Curtis
was gonna make it.

51:49.986 --> 51:52.784
But he didn't make it,
so I just wanted to try-

51:52.889 --> 51:55.357
I just wanted this one to make it.

51:58.860 --> 52:01.488
We were able to repair the cartilage.

52:01.596 --> 52:03.496
Okay?

52:11.840 --> 52:15.469
When basketball is over,
William may not have a friend in the world.

52:16.912 --> 52:19.642
Curtis lost his job as a security guard...

52:19.748 --> 52:22.774
and has been unemployed
for over four months.

52:22.884 --> 52:25.751
Sometimes I sit around
and my eyes just kinda get watery...

52:25.854 --> 52:28.720
'cause I be, like,
I ain't amounted to nothing.

52:28.823 --> 52:31.087
You know, I ain't got nothing.

52:31.192 --> 52:36.528
I can't even go out there and get a job
making seven dollars an hour.

52:37.698 --> 52:41.156
I'll be sitting there telling myself,
"You ain't gonna get no better. '"

52:48.609 --> 52:51.237
What did y'all tell me about
after y'all go to college and everything...

52:51.345 --> 52:53.245
y'all get your own place?

52:53.347 --> 52:55.837
We can all go to Arby's, baby.!

52:55.949 --> 52:58.975
- And get fresh Matt's Cookies.
- And going to Jewelâ€™s for our meat.

52:59.085 --> 53:03.454
- That's a lot of food stamps.
- We ain't gonna need no food stamps.

53:05.024 --> 53:07.720
Each day is a struggle.

53:07.827 --> 53:10.421
Trying to deal with the kids' attitudes
as well as my own...

53:10.530 --> 53:13.431
and trying to be strong enough
for them and myself.

53:13.533 --> 53:15.797
- That is so neat.
- I forgot to turn in my work.

53:15.902 --> 53:18.462
That is what you call a neat paper.
Yeah, that's neat.

53:18.571 --> 53:21.369
Don't you say that about my son.

53:21.474 --> 53:23.601
My son got a brain.
Now, you cut that out.

53:23.710 --> 53:25.836
- But he don't use it.
- See that brain there?

53:25.944 --> 53:28.606
Now there are two
new members of the Agee household.

53:28.714 --> 53:33.174
Arthur's sister Tomika
has a baby girl named Jazz.

53:33.285 --> 53:36.743
And Arthur's best friend Shannon moved in
to escape his own troubled home.

53:37.923 --> 53:39.982
Shannon is like me.

53:40.092 --> 53:42.560
He understood me,
and I understood him.

53:44.530 --> 53:46.998
He could sit back and talk to me
'cause I was his best friend.

53:47.099 --> 53:48.999
He trusted me, and I trust him.

53:51.403 --> 53:55.361
It's been crazy, as far as his father
and his mother's breakup.

53:55.473 --> 54:00.410
He'll come home,
and Bo stealing and buying drugs...

54:00.511 --> 54:02.945
and beat on his mother and stuff.

54:05.516 --> 54:08.542
You have to call the police
or get an order of protection...

54:08.653 --> 54:10.621
for him to leave me alone.

54:29.706 --> 54:32.869
My father was the same way.

54:32.976 --> 54:36.104
I think about it all the time,
when you come home, and they fightin'.

54:36.213 --> 54:39.239
You know, that gets to a child's head.

54:39.349 --> 54:42.250
They can't - Especially when you're
living with your mother...

54:42.352 --> 54:45.788
and you young,
and that's all you see all the time.

54:47.791 --> 54:50.555
He had to do something
to keep his spirit up.

54:56.632 --> 54:58.600
Ahh!

55:05.074 --> 55:06.974
Why you -

55:10.379 --> 55:14.816
Starting at guard,
number 11, a junior, Arthur Agee.!

55:14.917 --> 55:17.477
When I played basketball,
I knew what I wanted to do.

55:18.520 --> 55:20.488
This is what I want, you know.

55:20.588 --> 55:23.557
This is what I wanna do
for the rest of my life.

55:28.396 --> 55:30.261
Come on, win it, boy!

55:34.736 --> 55:36.636
Get that ball.!

55:38.606 --> 55:41.473
He's way behind
where I think he should be at this point.

55:41.576 --> 55:43.840
I've had a few guys come
to me from college -

55:43.945 --> 55:46.470
"Ooh, I like that kid.
He's quick, he's fast."

55:46.581 --> 55:48.913
But something's missing with Art.

55:56.723 --> 55:58.691
Shannon was on the basketball team too.

55:58.792 --> 56:02.558
He was a little more raw
than Arthur is.

56:02.663 --> 56:04.631
I couldn't handle two guys like that...

56:04.731 --> 56:08.098
so I tried the lesser of the evils.

56:08.201 --> 56:10.101
That was Arthur.

56:14.641 --> 56:17.166
Marshall's won six and lost 14...

56:17.277 --> 56:19.744
their worst record in 20 years.

56:19.845 --> 56:22.177
You just in a hurry to do nothing...

56:22.281 --> 56:25.216
'cause that's exactly
what you're doing - nothing.

56:31.190 --> 56:33.715
After spending
most of the game on the bench...

56:33.826 --> 56:36.386
Arthur gets another chance.

56:36.495 --> 56:39.692
Get that ball.! Work that ball, boy.!

56:39.799 --> 56:43.200
Yes.! That's the way you do it.!

56:45.104 --> 56:47.299
In the final minutes of a close game...

56:47.406 --> 56:50.306
Arthur takes it strong to the hoop.

56:52.277 --> 56:55.405
He's called for charging
and fouls out of the game.

57:16.167 --> 57:19.602
- There's been some bad calls all day.
- Amen!

57:19.703 --> 57:22.570
I'm telling you. Oh!

57:41.525 --> 57:43.652
The daily regimen of rehabilitation...

57:43.761 --> 57:46.092
is not the only change
in William's life.

57:49.365 --> 57:51.265
Say "hey!"

57:51.367 --> 57:53.301
- hey!
- Say "hey!"

57:58.374 --> 58:02.868
I was just basically scared to tell people.

58:02.979 --> 58:05.038
I was feelin' sick, you know...

58:05.148 --> 58:07.048
holding all this stuff
inside of me.

58:07.150 --> 58:09.050
I couldn't let it out.

58:10.086 --> 58:13.544
When I did finally tell Coach,
he was like, "When did this come about?'"

58:13.656 --> 58:14.587
And I said...

58:14.689 --> 58:17.658
"Oh... three, four months ago."

58:19.795 --> 58:21.820
he was like,
"Three or four months ago?"

58:23.265 --> 58:25.165
I was in the delivery room.

58:25.267 --> 58:27.167
The nurses gave her to her...

58:27.269 --> 58:30.170
and she handed the baby to me,
you know.

58:30.272 --> 58:33.173
And I'll never forget
how hard she was squeezing my hand.

58:35.277 --> 58:38.269
Once we got her home
William offered his help and stuff...

58:38.380 --> 58:41.838
but it was almost like I didn't want it
'cause she was mine.

58:41.950 --> 58:44.144
You know?
Instead of the two of us.

58:44.251 --> 58:49.018
So then, after a while we -
I finally let him keep her.

58:49.123 --> 58:51.250
And he earned his title.

58:51.358 --> 58:54.122
You smell good.

59:18.618 --> 59:21.348
Your numbers look real good.

59:21.454 --> 59:25.254
I think you're two to three weeks away
from being able to practice full.

59:25.358 --> 59:28.919
- You know what I mean?
- Two or three weeks?

59:29.028 --> 59:31.080
I know you wanted to waltz in here today

59:31.081 --> 59:33.658
and I'd tell you to go back
to practice right now...

59:33.766 --> 59:36.599
but I don't want it
to have to tear again.

59:37.837 --> 59:41.636
I felt that this was the year for me.

59:53.719 --> 59:57.314
I know we can make it downstate.

59:57.422 --> 59:59.754
That's just a big dream I done had.

01:00:03.428 --> 01:00:06.056
I look up on the scoreboard-

01:00:07.166 --> 01:00:10.033
My name is not even on there anymore.

01:00:12.203 --> 01:00:15.172
Where do I fit in with this team?

01:00:22.513 --> 01:00:24.913
William takes a makeup exam in math...

01:00:25.016 --> 01:00:27.211
because he skipped the final.

01:00:32.690 --> 01:00:35.955
Here's the cutoff point for passing.

01:00:37.395 --> 01:00:40.124
And you ended up right there.

01:00:40.230 --> 01:00:42.755
So you passed the final - barely.

01:00:42.866 --> 01:00:47.826
When I stopped playing ball,
all my grades just sunk.

01:00:48.939 --> 01:00:52.340
I understand we, uh -
we got the A.C.T. results.

01:00:52.442 --> 01:00:54.342
Yeah.

01:00:54.444 --> 01:00:57.675
Not as good as we, uh -
we wanted, huh?

01:01:03.553 --> 01:01:07.011
William scores a 15 on his first A.C. T.

01:01:07.123 --> 01:01:11.024
He needs to score an 18 to qualify
for an athletic scholarship...

01:01:11.126 --> 01:01:13.026
