02:05:50.202 --> 02:05:52.295
I'll be excited when I get there.

02:05:52.404 --> 02:05:55.099
That's when you'll be
excited the whole year.

02:05:55.206 --> 02:05:59.074
I'll be excited as soon as I step up
in there - first day of practice.

02:06:00.545 --> 02:06:03.571
If I graduate, I think I'll be
the only one in my family...

02:06:03.681 --> 02:06:06.514
besides my uncle,
to finish college.

02:06:06.617 --> 02:06:08.812
Me too.

02:06:11.422 --> 02:06:13.947
In the fourth round
against heavily favored Taft...

02:06:14.058 --> 02:06:17.027
Marshall meets their first
true test of the play-offs.

02:06:21.199 --> 02:06:23.928
But the Commandos have been
bucking the odds all year.

02:06:34.044 --> 02:06:37.172
Arthur plays one of his best games
of the season...

02:06:37.280 --> 02:06:39.180
scoring 19 points...

02:06:39.282 --> 02:06:42.740
and the Commandos claim a spot
in the city semifinals.

02:06:53.362 --> 02:06:58.390
The final four! I told y'all
he was going all the way. All the way!

02:06:58.501 --> 02:07:01.197
Do you guys feel you can play with
any team in the city?

02:07:01.303 --> 02:07:03.999
On any given day, we can play with anybody.
We can beat anybody.

02:07:15.684 --> 02:07:18.209
Marshall now faces
the ultimate test::

02:07:18.320 --> 02:07:21.720
King high School,
the rulers of the public league.

02:07:23.825 --> 02:07:25.920
Winners of last year's state crown,

02:07:25.921 --> 02:07:28.694
they were labeled the
best team in the country.

02:07:28.797 --> 02:07:32.460
King has sparked controversy
by out-recruiting rivals...

02:07:32.567 --> 02:07:35.730
for the biggest and best
grammar school players.

02:07:35.837 --> 02:07:40.274
We don't understand what
we're really doing to these young kids.

02:07:40.375 --> 02:07:42.275
Kid not even 12 years old...

02:07:42.377 --> 02:07:44.607
and you're baiting him
to come to your school...

02:07:44.712 --> 02:07:46.612
you know, to play basketball.

02:07:46.714 --> 02:07:48.807
Falls back in the paint.

02:07:48.917 --> 02:07:51.612
I'm not going to start
recruiting in that manner.

02:07:51.718 --> 02:07:55.017
No, I'll probably get out
of the game before then.

02:07:57.324 --> 02:07:59.724
The winner of these two semifinal games...

02:07:59.827 --> 02:08:03.786
will play for the Chicago Public
high School Basketball Championship.

02:08:09.570 --> 02:08:14.940
King's strategy is to
go inside to its two seven-foot starters.

02:08:19.378 --> 02:08:22.814
Only Arthur seems
unintimidated by the Jaguars.

02:08:28.988 --> 02:08:31.752
And King's poor play
keeps the game close.

02:08:32.792 --> 02:08:35.386
We are the... best.!
We are the team!

02:08:35.495 --> 02:08:37.622
I think they gonna take it.

02:08:38.664 --> 02:08:42.122
But in the second half,
King makes their move.

02:08:45.938 --> 02:08:48.098
- What are you doin'?
- Come on. Get in the game.!

02:08:48.206 --> 02:08:50.640
King grabs a four-point lead.

02:08:50.742 --> 02:08:53.142
Hey, Mookie, Mookie, Mookie!

02:08:53.245 --> 02:08:55.577
Y'all playing
with no confidence whatsoever.

02:08:55.680 --> 02:08:57.614
None!

02:08:57.716 --> 02:09:00.014
None.!

02:09:00.118 --> 02:09:03.019
- All right! Go get in charge of that ball!
- Don't foul him! Don't foul him!

02:09:07.859 --> 02:09:09.326
Let's go! Let's go!

02:09:09.427 --> 02:09:12.362
The Commandos get aggressive on defense...

02:09:12.464 --> 02:09:14.659
Too soon now!

02:09:14.766 --> 02:09:17.825
And use their superior speed on offense.

02:09:29.613 --> 02:09:32.741
Players, sit down.
We got three minutes to go. Sit down.

02:09:32.850 --> 02:09:35.944
Marshall grabs a six-point lead
late in the game.

02:09:36.053 --> 02:09:38.044
We got a long time to play.

02:09:39.423 --> 02:09:42.551
Coach Bedford wants to force King
out of their zone defense...

02:09:42.660 --> 02:09:46.993
and make their big, slow players match up
man-to-man against Marshall's quick guards.

02:09:47.096 --> 02:09:49.496
One, two, three. Defense!

02:09:53.369 --> 02:09:56.702
Arthur simply holds the ball
as the clock ticks away.

02:10:03.179 --> 02:10:05.807
The King coach has no choice.

02:10:24.933 --> 02:10:28.596
For the defending national champions,
it's all over.

02:10:34.376 --> 02:10:37.641
And unranked Marshall
will play for the city title.

02:10:55.263 --> 02:10:59.461
Whoo! 26-2 now!

02:11:01.235 --> 02:11:03.669
They're 26 and 2 now.

02:11:03.771 --> 02:11:06.296
That's my Man!

02:11:07.341 --> 02:11:09.639
All right, Man!

02:11:09.744 --> 02:11:11.644
- I told you we could do it.
- Yes!

02:11:11.746 --> 02:11:14.475
- I told you we could do it.
- I told you you were gonna do it.

02:11:14.581 --> 02:11:16.481
I knew y'all was going all the way.
I told ya.

02:11:16.583 --> 02:11:18.483
I said, "You're going all the way."

02:11:19.519 --> 02:11:22.886
This is your last year.
You're going all the way. Yeah.

02:11:24.958 --> 02:11:28.052
They got the best shot of him, you know.

02:11:28.161 --> 02:11:31.562
And it's great.
That was a great shot, wasn't it?

02:11:31.665 --> 02:11:36.193
But this one in the, uh, Tribune
is what I really like.

02:11:36.303 --> 02:11:40.103
It says,
"Arthur Agee stood as still as a statue.

02:11:40.206 --> 02:11:43.572
Time after time was on his side."

02:11:43.676 --> 02:11:47.009
You know, the championship
that I missed when I was in high school-

02:11:47.112 --> 02:11:49.012
Yeah.

02:11:49.114 --> 02:11:52.743
Twenty-one years later I got a chance
at getting a championship through him.

02:11:52.851 --> 02:11:55.376
You know, you're always trying to
build your children up...

02:11:55.487 --> 02:11:57.387
and saying, "Well, you-all can do it"...

02:11:57.489 --> 02:12:00.287
but, you know, really lying on
the inside a little bit, saying...

02:12:00.392 --> 02:12:02.292
"Well, you know, you got a long haul."

02:12:02.394 --> 02:12:04.453
But, you know,
this make you even more confidence...

02:12:04.563 --> 02:12:07.498
because if he's sure of hisself,
then you know you can bank on it.

02:12:07.599 --> 02:12:12.092
Yesterday, you know, when he won the game,
you know, he told me he loved me.

02:12:12.203 --> 02:12:14.865
And, you know, I haven't heard that
in, uh -You know.

02:12:14.972 --> 02:12:19.409
You can feel it, but I haven't heard it
coming verbally from him.

02:12:30.021 --> 02:12:33.479
In a rematch with rival Westinghouse...

02:12:33.591 --> 02:12:37.652
Marshall proves to everybody
they have what it takes to be city champs.

02:12:37.762 --> 02:12:40.594
Inside pass. Shot rejected.

02:12:44.935 --> 02:12:47.802
To the lane with the layin.

02:12:47.904 --> 02:12:50.668
Busts this game wide open.

02:12:50.774 --> 02:12:55.143
Did you see that?
Did you see it? Did you see it?

02:12:56.613 --> 02:12:59.673
They are celebrating because they know...

02:12:59.783 --> 02:13:02.809
their high school is headed
to the elite eight in Champaign.

02:13:06.490 --> 02:13:10.289
And the Marshall Commandos
have won the Public League Championship...

02:13:10.393 --> 02:13:12.520
in convincing fashion-

02:13:12.628 --> 02:13:17.622
58-38 winners over
the Westinghouse Warriors.

02:13:31.614 --> 02:13:34.549
What's up, man?
Told you on the phone what I was gonna do.

02:13:34.650 --> 02:13:36.618
Told you, boy.

02:13:39.788 --> 02:13:42.586
Marshall, baby. Marshall!

02:13:42.690 --> 02:13:44.590
Marshall!

02:13:44.692 --> 02:13:48.492
Marshall.! Marshall.!

02:13:48.596 --> 02:13:52.430
Marshall.! Marshall.!

02:13:59.574 --> 02:14:03.567
Your A.C.T. came in, William,
and you received a 14 for a composite...

02:14:03.678 --> 02:14:05.873
which is not high enough.

02:14:05.980 --> 02:14:08.709
Uh, you've taken the test-
Now, this was for the fourth time.

02:14:08.816 --> 02:14:12.308
Now, if you add all those up,
it comes out to 17.2.

02:14:12.419 --> 02:14:15.183
In order to play at Marquette,
you're gonna have to get the 18.

02:14:15.289 --> 02:14:17.189
And they're very, very concerned.

02:14:17.291 --> 02:14:21.227
One assistant called twice this week,
and Bo Ellis called today.

02:14:23.363 --> 02:14:25.991
Smile, William.
It's not the end of the world.

02:14:26.099 --> 02:14:28.033
- Right?
- I hope not.

02:14:28.135 --> 02:14:31.366
Well, you gotta work at this
as hard as you worked at your jump shot.

02:14:31.472 --> 02:14:33.963
And it was missing a lot this year.

02:14:34.074 --> 02:14:36.041
Okay.

02:14:36.142 --> 02:14:39.669
Now you are down to the final inning
and the last strike.

02:14:46.118 --> 02:14:49.053
We're going, going downstate!
We're going downstate!

02:14:49.155 --> 02:14:52.318
Now let's, let's celebrate!
Now let's celebrate!

02:14:52.425 --> 02:14:55.189
- What are we gonna be?
- State champions.!

02:14:55.294 --> 02:14:58.161
Your Marshall Commandos.!

02:15:02.568 --> 02:15:04.660
- Yeah!
- We're gonna take state!

02:15:04.769 --> 02:15:06.930
Take state! Number one!

02:15:32.831 --> 02:15:35.663
Beat B-A - B-A-T-A-V-I-A.!

02:15:35.766 --> 02:15:38.758
Beat B-A - B-A-T-A-V-I-A.!

02:15:38.869 --> 02:15:42.965
Beat B-A - B-A-T-A-V-I-A!

02:15:52.016 --> 02:15:56.043
Downstate Marshall plays
its familiar role as underdog...

02:15:56.153 --> 02:15:58.053
to third-ranked Batavia.

02:15:58.155 --> 02:16:00.055
Justice has it. Justice, one-on-two.

02:16:00.157 --> 02:16:02.750
- Spins up-
- Nice move.

02:16:06.663 --> 02:16:10.724
In the media glare of a statewide
audience, Marshall shows big-game jitters.

02:16:10.833 --> 02:16:12.767
Now bust out.

02:16:12.869 --> 02:16:15.702
And Marshall missed the layup.

02:16:17.206 --> 02:16:19.640
Sealed off, blocked by Williams.

02:16:19.742 --> 02:16:23.644
You got easy shots.
You gotta make your easy shots.

02:16:23.746 --> 02:16:25.714
I can't shoot for you.

02:16:25.815 --> 02:16:30.514
Now he's gonna penetrate.
Left it for Christian. Missed the shot.

02:16:30.620 --> 02:16:35.522
Luther Bedford looks like
he's ready to commit suicide over there.

02:16:35.624 --> 02:16:38.218
Y'all better get on your job,
Commandos!

02:16:38.326 --> 02:16:40.454
- Now into the corner.
- Get in there.

02:16:40.562 --> 02:16:43.929
Batavia's got these guys on the run.

02:16:46.034 --> 02:16:47.933
One, one, one, one!

02:16:48.036 --> 02:16:50.504
One, one, one, one.!

02:16:51.974 --> 02:16:55.034
But in the third quarter,
the Commandos charge back.

02:16:55.143 --> 02:16:57.043
And a steal by Marshall.!

02:16:57.145 --> 02:16:59.841
Agee gonna take it all the way.

02:16:59.948 --> 02:17:04.111
Yes! That's the way you go!

02:17:04.218 --> 02:17:06.379
- here we go.
- Picked him clean.

02:17:06.486 --> 02:17:08.421
Dale. Marshall leads.

02:17:08.522 --> 02:17:11.616
Marshall's first lead
since the first quarter.

02:17:11.726 --> 02:17:14.718
Like a lightning bolt,
the Commandos have struck.

02:17:14.829 --> 02:17:18.356
37-36, Marshall leading Batavia.

02:17:18.466 --> 02:17:21.196
Chicago Marshall has exploded-

02:17:25.940 --> 02:17:27.874
I always dreamed of, like...

02:17:27.975 --> 02:17:30.772
me and William taking
them downstate together.

02:17:31.878 --> 02:17:33.778
When I was at St. Joseph...

02:17:33.879 --> 02:17:36.474
maybe we could have went downstate,
and maybe we couldn't.

02:17:36.583 --> 02:17:39.518
But we did when I'm at Marshall.

02:17:53.133 --> 02:17:55.727
Arthur's big fourth quarter
helps add Batavia...

02:17:55.834 --> 02:17:57.769
to Marshall's growing list of upsets.

02:17:57.870 --> 02:18:01.465
Spectacular comeback
in the fourth quarter by the Commandos-

02:18:01.573 --> 02:18:03.473
In the post-game news conference...

02:18:03.575 --> 02:18:06.772
Coach Bedford labels
his unranked team "the giant killers. '"

02:18:10.782 --> 02:18:13.513
- Y'all are playing the number one team.
- We're playing the number one team.

02:18:13.619 --> 02:18:15.519
We're playing the number two team.

02:18:15.620 --> 02:18:19.489
This is the first time in the history
of the school that we've gone this far.

02:18:19.591 --> 02:18:22.218
- Really?
- In the history of the school.

02:18:22.326 --> 02:18:24.692
Just like the Commandos.
See, we been the underdog.

02:18:24.797 --> 02:18:28.197
I'm glad we are because then
it just show you how you could come up.

02:18:28.299 --> 02:18:30.824
And then you beat your opponent.

02:18:33.037 --> 02:18:35.267
Oh, yeah.

02:18:49.187 --> 02:18:52.179
Be a good place for Man to come.

02:18:52.290 --> 02:18:55.452
Yeah. This is really, you know,
something that a -

02:18:55.559 --> 02:18:58.153
a child would really miss out on.

02:18:58.261 --> 02:19:00.821
Like a whole different world.

02:19:00.931 --> 02:19:02.922
It's beyond different.

02:19:03.032 --> 02:19:05.661
Uh-huh.

02:19:13.744 --> 02:19:17.544
In this semifinal game,
we'll see some great individuals...

02:19:17.647 --> 02:19:19.672
just as we saw many years ago.

02:19:19.782 --> 02:19:22.752
Remember Isiah Thomas,
one of the great guards.

02:19:22.852 --> 02:19:26.253
Here you see the same moves
he plays with in the NBA today.

02:19:26.355 --> 02:19:30.348
Well, we've got someone like that:
howard Nathan, number 34...

02:19:30.459 --> 02:19:32.393
for Peoria Manual.

02:19:32.495 --> 02:19:34.588
Marshall got here because of
one reason: quickness.

02:19:34.697 --> 02:19:38.826
The reason: Arthur Agee.
Look at this man. he just explodes, Dan.

02:19:38.933 --> 02:19:42.630
He can get down court
as quick as anyone I've ever seen.

02:19:42.737 --> 02:19:44.638
In the semifinals...

02:19:44.740 --> 02:19:48.107
Arthur goes head-to-head
with howard Nathan, the all-American.

02:19:48.209 --> 02:19:51.236
Make him work for it, Man.
Make him work for what he get.

02:19:52.281 --> 02:19:55.408
All right! Let's go!
All the way, Man! All the way!

02:19:56.751 --> 02:19:59.743
Yeah! That's it! That's it! That's it!

02:19:59.854 --> 02:20:04.484
Arthur Agee, spinning inside,
tough shot. Good.

02:20:04.592 --> 02:20:06.787
Arthur has a great first half...

02:20:06.895 --> 02:20:09.125
but the Rams play even better.

02:20:10.799 --> 02:20:13.199
He's got it.

02:20:14.235 --> 02:20:16.931
Get up for the Rams!
Everybody get up!

02:20:17.038 --> 02:20:19.302
Get up for the Rams.!

02:20:19.407 --> 02:20:22.934
In the second half,
Arthur tries to pick up where he left off.

02:20:23.044 --> 02:20:24.807
Penetration move by Agee. Slapped

02:20:24.808 --> 02:20:27.207
out of there by Manual.
They've got two-on-one.

02:20:27.314 --> 02:20:30.249
Ooh, and a nice fake and a score.

02:20:30.350 --> 02:20:33.183
But it's the Rams who don't miss a beat...

02:20:33.287 --> 02:20:35.221
pressing the tempo against
the tired Commandos.

02:20:35.322 --> 02:20:37.984
You're not in the offense at all.

02:20:38.091 --> 02:20:40.719
You're just out there
playing individual basketball.

02:20:40.828 --> 02:20:42.728
Completely.

02:20:42.830 --> 02:20:46.857
Hey, hey, guys. No fouls.
We want to keep the clock going. Remember?

02:20:46.967 --> 02:20:48.992
Let's go, Marshall!
Let's go!

02:20:49.102 --> 02:20:51.832
Let's go, Marshall.!
Let's go.!

02:20:51.939 --> 02:20:55.032
Marshall showed us last night
they have the ability to come back.

02:20:55.141 --> 02:20:57.132
Let's see what they can do here.

02:21:11.791 --> 02:21:13.884
This is Nathan.

02:21:13.993 --> 02:21:15.893
Nice pass.
Knock it down.

02:21:15.995 --> 02:21:19.795
Biggest lead of the game now,
and the Rams fans can smell it.

02:21:21.299 --> 02:21:24.166
Been a great run
for Luther Bedford's team.

02:21:25.203 --> 02:21:27.569
The string of upsets stops here.

02:21:29.207 --> 02:21:32.199
- And a foul on Agee.
- He fouls out.

02:21:32.310 --> 02:21:35.473
But he just never quit.
He just kept going for the basketball.

02:21:40.418 --> 02:21:44.878
I wouldn't be surprised
if he made the all-tournament team tonight.

02:22:05.209 --> 02:22:07.734
- Number one!
- We're number one.!

02:22:07.845 --> 02:22:09.779
We're still number one.

02:22:09.880 --> 02:22:11.780
All right. All right.

02:22:11.882 --> 02:22:13.873
Though they lose to Peoria Manual...

02:22:13.984 --> 02:22:19.115
they finish third in the state, the highest
a Marshall team has finished since 1960.

02:22:21.691 --> 02:22:25.149
This was a great season you had.

02:22:25.261 --> 02:22:30.358
There is nothing sweeter
than going downstate as a young person.

02:22:30.466 --> 02:22:32.832
I mean, the record's
gonna stay there, you know.

02:22:32.936 --> 02:22:36.303
1991, there was a team
from Marshall played.

02:22:36.406 --> 02:22:38.636
- You know, and you're part of that.
- Yeah.

02:22:38.741 --> 02:22:40.868
- That's part of history.
- Ah!

02:22:40.977 --> 02:22:44.140
